    Class ProtobufTransform2d

    Represents a 2D coordinate transformation.

    This message describes how to transform coordinates from one 2D coordinate frame to another. It combines a translation and rotation to define the relationship between two coordinate systems.

    Mathematical Interpretation: Given a point P in frame A, the corresponding point in frame B is: P_B = Transform2d * P_A = Rotation * P_A + Translation

    Applications:

    • Transform between robot and field coordinate frames
    • Relative positioning between objects
    • Coordinate frame conversions in path planning
    • Sensor calibration and mounting offsets

    The transform represents "how to get from frame A to frame B" and can be inverted to get the reverse transformation.

    Rotation

    Rotation component of the transformation.

    This represents the angular difference between the two coordinate frames. It specifies how much the target frame is rotated relative to the source frame.

    The rotation is applied before the translation in the transformation sequence (standard mathematical convention).

    Declaration
    public ProtobufRotation2d Rotation { get; set; }
    Property Value
    Type Description
    ProtobufRotation2d

    Translation

    Translation component of the transformation.

    This represents the displacement between the origins of the two coordinate frames. It specifies how far and in which direction the target frame's origin is from the source frame's origin.
